.TH SSHKNOCKD 8 "" "sshknockd 0.2.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
sshknockd \- server-side port knocking daemon for SSH access control
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sshknockd
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.br
.B sshknockd
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR] \fBsetup-firewall\fR
.br
.B sshknockd
\fBupdate\fR
.br
.B sshknockd
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR] \fBconfig\fR
.br
.B sshknockd
\fBversion\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sshknockd
listens for a configured TCP, UDP, or ICMP knock sequence and temporarily allows the source IP to reach the configured SSH TCP port through ipset and iptables rules.
.PP
The knock sequence is not authentication. SSH authentication remains the security boundary.
.PP
The product flow is clientless. Clients reproduce the configured knock sequence with common tools such as nc, ping, shell redirection, or SSH ProxyCommand; sshknockd does not provide client helper commands.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup-firewall
Creates the configured allow and ban ipsets and installs iptables or ip6tables rules for the protected SSH port.
.TP
.B update
Fetches the latest GitHub release from the built-in repository, compares it with the installed version, selects a DEB or RPM package for the current Linux distribution and CPU architecture, installs it, and restarts the sshknockd systemd service.
.TP
.B config
Prints a short summary of the loaded configuration.
.TP
.B version
Prints the installed sshknockd version.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/sshknockd.toml
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/log/sshknockd/sshknockd.log
Default SIEM-oriented audit log file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ssh (1),
.BR nc (1),
.BR iptables (8),
.BR ip6tables (8),
.BR ipset (8),
.BR systemctl (1)
